---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What is TripLion Map?',
    answer: 'TripLion Map is our trip planner. It keeps your itinerary and your map in one view, so you can plan routes, stays, and stops without juggling separate apps.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is TripLion Map in beta?',
    answer: 'Not yet. The product is currently in pre-release, before beta testing opens. Join the waitlist and we will email you as access rolls out.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How is this different from just using Google Maps?',
    answer: 'Google Maps handles navigation. TripLion Map handles the planning around it: the itinerary, the stops you are considering, notes, and reservations, all connected to the same map, with a one-click handoff to Google Maps when it is time to drive.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What does AI-assisted discovery actually do?',
    answer: 'You can describe what you want in plain language, like a quiet beach or a quick food stop near the highway, and get suggestions that stay relevant to your route instead of generic results from anywhere.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I plan trips with other people?',
    answer: 'Yes. Share a trip with friends and let them edit the same itinerary with you, so the plan stays in one place instead of scattered across messages.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can I keep notes and reservations in the plan?',
    answer: 'Yes. Add notes and reservation details directly to a specific destination, so booking confirmations and reminders stay with the place they belong to.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Will it cost anything?',
    answer: 'TripLion Map is free to use during pre-release. We will be upfront well before anything changes.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Is my trip data private and secure?',
    answer: 'Your data is encrypted in transit and at rest. By default, only you can see your trips; you choose who to share a plan with, and can revoke access at any time.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I get help if something breaks?',
    answer: 'Email hello@trip-lion.com or use the contact form. We read every message ourselves.',
  },
];
---
<Layout
  title="Q&A — TripLion Map"
  description="Answers to common questions about TripLion Map: pre-release status, AI-assisted discovery, navigation, sharing, reservations, pricing, and data security."
  path="/q-and-a"
>
  <main class="qa-page">
    <section class="container qa-inner">
      <h1>Q&A</h1>
      <p>Answers to what people ask us most. Still stuck? <a href="/contact">Contact us</a>.</p>
      <div class="faq-list">
        {faqs.map((faq, index) => (
          <details open={index === 0}>
            <summary>{faq.question}</summary>
            <p>{faq.answer}</p>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
